The paper discusses methods of context-tree prediction for individual sequences, which involves predicting the next outcome based on a context of past outcomes. This is a problem that falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the asymptotic regime, which suggests a focus on theoretical analysis and complexity, further supporting the likelihood of cs.IT and cs.DS as top categories.
